\b\fs28 \cf0 Features and Usage
\fs24 \

\b0 This shader is the basic version of all foliage shaders and supports procedural wind animation, physically based shading and physically based wetness.\
It can be used one single game objects but i highly recommend to always use the "Combine Children Afs" script as it will not only reduce the number of draw calls and speed up rendering but also give you much more variety.\
In order to be able to use the shader with your own meshes latter have to fit its needs descried in the "AFS Model and Texture Guide.pdf". And just to give you a brief overview: You have to have double sided geometry on thin = translucent parts like leaves and have to add vertex colors (and may be even UV4 coordinates), which control bending. Add those manually or use the Afs foliage tool to do so.\
