\b\fs24 Specular Reflectivity (Color)
\b0 \
\'84Specular Reflectivity\'93 equals \'84Specular Color\'93 (when using the standard shader and the specular setup). In physically based shading the specular color describes the \'84base reflectivity\'93 of a material determining the minimum amount of light that is reflected when looking at it from an angle of 0 degrees. This base reflectivity gains up to 100% percent at grazing angles (which is known as fresnel reflection).\
As plants usually have a non metal but dielectric surface this should be set to a rather dark gray.\
Please keep in mind: When talking about specular reflections the most important input will be a nice and proper roughness/smoothness map.\

\fs12 \

\b\fs24 Translucency Color
\b0 \
The color that will be added on top when the leaves are backlit.\

\fs12 \

\b\fs24 View Dependency
\b0 \
Fully view dependent translucency is relative to the angle between the view direction and the light direction. View independent is relative to the angle between the leaf's normal vector and the light direction.\

\fs12 \

\b\fs24 Leaf Turbulence
\b0 \
Increasing Leaf Turbulence will make those parts of the plant which are effected by secondary bending sway faster if the wind blows stronger.\
The per material Leaf Turbulence factor will be multiplied with vertex color red so you will get some variation between different leaves o fthe same plant. Please make sure taht vertex color red is not set to 0.0.\

\fs12 \

